#. type: Title =
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Secure Infinispan server by default"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:13
msgid "The Infinispan server we introduced in 10.0 exposes a single port through which both Hot Rod and HTTP clients can connect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:15
msgid "While Infinispan has had *very* extensive security support since 7.0, the out-of-the-box default configuration did not enable authentication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:18
msgid "Infinispan 11.0's server's default configuration, instead, requires authentication.  We have made several improvements to how authentication is configured and the tooling we provide to make the experience as smooth as possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Automatic authentication mechanism selection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:22
msgid "Previously, when enabling authentication, you had to explicitly define which mechanisms had to be enabled per-protocol, with all of the peculiarities specific to each one (i.e. SASL for Hot Rod, HTTP for REST). Here is an example configuration with Infinispan 10.1 that enables DIGEST authentication:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<endpoints socket-binding=\"default\" security-realm=\"default\">\n"
"   <hotrod-connector name=\"hotrod\">\n"
"      <authentication>\n"
"         <sasl mechanisms=\"DIGEST-MD5\" server-name=\"infinispan\"/>\n"
"      </authentication>\n"
"   </hotrod-connector>\n"
"   <rest-connector name=\"rest\">\n"
"      <authentication mechanisms=\"DIGEST\"/>\n"
"   </rest-connector>\n"
"</endpoints>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:38
msgid "In Infinispan 11.0, the mechanisms are automatically selected based on the capabilities of the security realm. Using the following configuration:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<endpoints socket-binding=\"default\" security-realm=\"default\">\n"
"   <hotrod-connector name=\"hotrod\" />\n"
"   <rest-connector name=\"rest\"/>\n"
"</endpoints>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:48
msgid "together with a properties security realm, will enable DIGEST for HTTP and SCRAM-+*+, DIGEST-+*+ and CRAM-MD5 for Hot Rod. BASIC/PLAIN will only be implicitly enabled when the security realm has a TLS/SSL identity."
msgstr ""

