msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:101
msgid "The properties realm that is part of the default configuration has been greatly improved in Infinispan 11. The passwords are now stored in multiple encrypted formats in order to support the various DIGEST, SCRAM and PLAIN/BASIC mechanisms."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:103
msgid "The `user` functionality that is now built into the CLI allows easy creation and manipulation of users, passwords and groups:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:116
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[disconnected]> user create --password=secret --groups=admin admin\n"
"[disconnected]> connect --username=admin --password=secret\n"
"[ispn-29934@cluster//containers/default]> user ls\n"
"[ \"admin\" ]\n"
"[ispn-29934@cluster//containers/default]> user describe admin\n"
"{ username: \"admin\", realm: \"default\", groups = [admin] }\n"
"[ispn-29934@cluster//containers/default]> user password admin\n"
"Set a password for the user: ******\n"
"Confirm the password for the user: ******\n"
"[ispn-29934@cluster//containers/default]>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Authorization: simplified"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:121
msgid "Authorization is another security aspect of Infinispan. In previous versions, setting up authorization was complicated by the need to add all the needed roles to each cache:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<infinispan>\n"
"   <cache-container name=\"default\">\n"
"      <security>\n"
"         <authorization>\n"
"            <identity-role-mapper/>\n"
"            <role name=\"AdminRole\" permissions=\"ALL\"/>\n"
"            <role name=\"ReaderRole\" permissions=\"READ\"/>\n"
"            <role name=\"WriterRole\" permissions=\"WRITE\"/>\n"
"            <role name=\"SupervisorRole\" permissions=\"READ WRITE EXEC BULK_READ\"/>\n"
"         </authorization>\n"
"      </security>\n"
"      <distributed-cache name=\"secured\">\n"
"         <security>\n"
"            <authorization roles=\"AdminRole ReaderRole WriterRole SupervisorRole\"/>\n"
"         </security>\n"
"      </distributed-cache>\n"
"   </cache-container>\n"
"   ...\n"
"</infinispan>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:146
msgid "With Infinispan 11 you can avoid specifying all the roles at the cache level: just enable authorization and all roles will implicitly apply. As you can see, the cache definition is much more concise:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_posts/2020-06-04-server-secure-by-default.adoc:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<infinispan>\n"
"   <cache-container name=\"default\">\n"
"      ...\n"
"      <distributed-cache name=\"secured\">\n"
"         <security>\n"
"            <authorization/>\n"
"         </security>\n"
"      </distributed-cache>\n"
"   </cache-container>\n"
"   ...\n"
"</infinispan>\n"
msgstr ""

